The paper presents a new modeling class for temporal processes, which is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of Bayesian Networks suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI), while the emphasis on temporal dynamics and irregularly spaced observations suggests a focus on signal processing and information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also discusses learning algorithms, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and possibly also social and information networks (cs.SI).
